]]></Script>
            <DialogOptions />
          </Dialog>
          <Dialog>
            <ID>4</ID>
            <Name>ds</Name>
            <ShowTextParser>False</ShowTextParser>
            <Script><![CDATA[// Dialog script file
@S  // Dialog startup entry point
soyus:Hey! We have arrived.
return
@1
soyus:Cool right! Going to Game Jams are fun!
return
@2
soyus:Don’t be nervous, just try to have fun!
bus:Guess no need to postpone it. It was time to do some great Jammin. 
bus:I tried to go to the cabin.
stop]]></Script>
            <DialogOptions>
              <DialogOption>
                <ID>1</ID>
                <Say>True</Say>
                <Show>True</Show>
                <Text xml:space="preserve">Oh wow</Text>
              </DialogOption>
              <DialogOption>
                <ID>2</ID>
                <Say>True</Say>
                <Show>True</Show>
                <Text xml:space="preserve">I’m kinda nervous</Text>
              </DialogOption>
            </DialogOptions>
          </Dialog>
          <Dialog>
            <ID>5</ID>
            <Name>bedroom</Name>
            <ShowTextParser>False</ShowTextParser>
            <Script><![CDATA[// Dialog script file
@S  // Dialog startup entry point
cRoger: In the room I saw my roommate. 
cRoger: She looked friendly, if a bit foxy. She waved at me.
return
@1
roommate:hm? Just make yourself at home. Ha ha ha >u<
return
@2
roommate:Hat? You’re pretty funny. Nice to meet you.

cRoger:The aura of the room felt strange
stop]]></Script>
            <DialogOptions>
              <DialogOption>
                <ID>1</ID>
                <Say>True</Say>
                <Show>True</Show>
                <Text xml:space="preserve">Hey roomie. You uhhh …</Text>
              </DialogOption>
              <DialogOption>
                <ID>2</ID>
                <Say>True</Say>
                <Show>True</Show>
                <Text xml:space="preserve">I like your hat, the design is cute</Text>
              </DialogOption>
            </DialogOptions>
          </Dialog>
          <Dialog>
            <ID>6</ID>
            <Name>de</Name>
            <ShowTextParser>False</ShowTextParser>
            <Script><![CDATA[// Dialog script file
@S  // Dialog startup entry point
cRoger:I can’t help but think that it all wasn’t just a trick of the mind. 
cRoger:Like I walked into another dimension. 
cRoger:Hmm strange, at least that’s all over now.
return
]]></Script>
